WASHINGTON A Canadian packing plant of IBP Inc. voluntarily recalled 46,000 pounds of ground beef products Saturday because of possible contamination with E. coli 0157:H7, the second recall in two days for the United States' largest beef processor.
Tuesday's recall is the third issued by the company, D'Artagnan, since Dec. 17 when it learned that its truffled foie gras mousse, which is sold in stores across the United States and Canada, through catalogs and over the Internet, had made two people in Maryland ill with listeriosis.
